    "created_at": "2016-07-14T17:48:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-14T17:48:52Z",
    "body": "> Enable node integration in the outer BrowserWindow? If you're only loading trusted content there, it should be fine, no?\n\n@paulcbetts It is presumably trusted content, but it also contains remote user data so XSS is a concern.\n\n> I don't know how browserhtml works, but if you don't trust the page to use node integration, you shouldn't trust it to use webview neither. Regardless whether we allow using preload attribute, merely having <webview> tag is going to cause security problems, it basically allows people to read everything on system.\n\n@zcbenz Interesting, I wasn't aware of that. Could we devise a way to limit the `src` and `preload` of a `webview` to a safe subset based on some `BrowserWindow` option? E.g. a callback function checks whether or not the `webview` `preload`/`src` values should be allowed. I would be happy to do the implementation work.\n"
  },
