    "created_at": "2016-07-15T02:11:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-15T02:11:05Z",
    "body": "> E.g. a callback function checks whether or not the webview preload/src values should be allowed. I would be happy to do the implementation work.\n\nSounds good to me, we can probably add 2 events to `WebContents`: `webview-created` and `will-create-webview`. The `will-create-webview` event can be used to strip out the `preload` option, and `webview-created` event can be used to add a listener to the `will-navigate` event of webview's WebContents to decide whether to navigate to a page.\n\nI'm merging this to #2749.\n\n> @zcbenz If nodeintegration is not enabled on the browser window, and am using a preload script, what is the security issue?\n\nIt should be as safe as running an un-sandboxed page in Chrome browser.\n"
  },
